Preheat oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C). Drop 1 teaspoon olive oil each into 6 muffin cups. Beat eggs, egg whites, and milk together in a glass bowl until smooth. Heat egg mixture in microwave oven until warmed, about 1 minute. Stir flour into the egg mixture until completely incorporated into a batter. Heat muffin cups in preheated oven until the oil is smoking, 2 to 3 minutes. Stir cold water into batter. Pour 1/4 cup batter into each muffin cup. Bake in the preheated oven until risen and cooked in their centers, about 25 minutes.